==English==

===Noun===
'''qualophile'''
# literally a lover of qualia
# a word used to label cognitive scientists that endorse qualia as being unmeasurable by [[heterophenomenology]]

===Quotations===

'''2005''' A high-level natural individual ''Deep Thoughts''
:"The real killer is this. Rosenberg set out to explain [[qualia]], but at the end of the day it seems to me your real '''qualophile''' would say: yes, that's all very interesting, Gregg - thing is, I can imagine all of that happening without my actually experiencing the real redness of red. I don't see anything in your theory which actually catches the vivid reality of [[subjective]] experience. Now of course, in my eyes all talk of [[qualia]] is so much hot air, but I don't see why that would be any less [[plausible]] than the case for qualia was in the first place." [http://www.consciousentities.com/rosenberg.htm]

'''1997''' Joseph Levine ''Consciousness Located: You'll Wonder Where the Yellow Went. Psycoloquy: 8(04)''
:"So what is the explanatory problem that bothers the '''qualophile''' (to use [[w:Daniel Dennett| Dennett's]] term)? Right now I'm looking at the red [[diskette]] case beside my computer. My perceptual state possesses a certain reddish [[qualitative]] character. What explains that feature of my [[perceptual]] state? " [http://www.cogsci.ecs.soton.ac.uk/cgi/psyc/newpsy?locating-consciousness.3]